Question:
How to do Gradient effect with cobimed image?

<!--more-->

Answer:
Well, firstly I try to use CSS but nothing works, so I try to use <em>linear-gradient</em> hand-by-hand in HTML page, but only shows gradient. Failed and failed again, I finally found this code:
<code>    &lt;div style="
width:640px;height:480px;
background:linear-gradient(toprgba(255,255,255,1),rgba(255,255,255,0)),url(/images/PosterSite_SamplePhoto.jpg) center bottom no-repeat;
background:-moz-linear-gradient(top,rgba(255,255,255,1),rgba(255,255,255,0)),url(/images/PosterSite_SamplePhoto.jpg) center bottom no-repeat;
background:-webkit-linear-gradient(top,rgba(255,255,255,1),rgba(255,255,255,0)),url(/images/PosterSite_SamplePhoto.jpg) center bottom no-repeat;
"&gt;&lt;!--//--&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code>
Try to like this:
<code>    &lt;div style="
width:1000px;height:300px;
background:linear-gradient(bottom,toprgba(0,0,0,1),rgba(0,0,0,0)),url(profile.png) center bottom no-repeat;
background:-moz-linear-gradient(bottom,rgba(0,0,0,1),rgba(0,0,0,0)),url(profile.png) center bottom no-repeat;
background:-webkit-linear-gradient(bottom,rgba(0,0,0,1),rgba(0,0,0,0)),url(profile.png) center bottom no-repeat;
"&gt;&lt;!--//--&gt; &lt;!--Line6: ;--&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code>
Success, but not really my image. Well next time I need to know how to let image scaled down.

